    <section id="urgency" class="section">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <div>
          <span class="section-label">MARKET CONTEXT</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">Deployment Environment</h2>
          <p class="section-lead">
            A gap exists between autonomous system deployment and independently verifiable runtime enforcement mechanisms. ODDC defines and attests to that category of verification.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal" style="max-width:700px;margin:0 auto;">
        <div class="hud-frame hud-scanline"><i></i>
          <div class="hud-label" style="margin-bottom:16px;">CONVERGENCE FACTORS</div>
          <div class="hud-row" style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:10px;">
            <span class="hud-dot hud-dot-amber" style="margin-top:5px;"></span>
            <div><span class="hud-title">Expanding Autonomous System Deployment</span>
            <div class="hud-desc">Autonomous systems with actuator authority are operating across transportation, finance, healthcare, and industrial automation. Many deployments rely on self-attested enforcement mechanisms.</div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="hud-row" style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:10px;">
            <span class="hud-dot hud-dot-amber" style="margin-top:5px;"></span>
            <div><span class="hud-title">Procurement Scrutiny Is Rising</span>
            <div class="hud-desc">Enterprise and government procurement committees increasingly require independent governance evidence — not vendor self-assessment.</div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="hud-row" style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:10px;">
            <span class="hud-dot hud-dot-red" style="margin-top:5px;"></span>
            <div><span class="hud-title">Self-Attestation Limitations</span>
            <div class="hud-desc">Publicized autonomous system incidents have increased scrutiny of self-attestation models. Procurement and governance review increasingly reference independent verification mechanisms.</div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="hud-row" style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:10px;">
            <span class="hud-dot hud-dot-amber" style="margin-top:5px;"></span>
            <div><span class="hud-title">Regulatory Framework Integration</span>
            <div class="hud-desc">Existing regulatory frameworks may incorporate independent runtime verification mechanisms. ODDC provides a referenceable standard compatible with existing approval structures.</div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="hud-row" style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:10px;">
            <span class="hud-dot hud-dot-red" style="margin-top:5px;"></span>
            <div><span class="hud-title">Governance and Liability Considerations</span>
            <div class="hud-desc">Deployment without independently verifiable enforcement introduces governance and liability considerations that structured conformance determination may address.</div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
